The French government will present toparliament a major bill within two months to overhaul the Parisstock market, economics and finance minister Edouard Balladursaid.    Balladur told an Economist conference that on the productside, a series of new contracts, including share options andforward contracts in European Currency Units (ECUs), would beintroduced shortly for trading on the Paris bourse.    The scope of the new bill, however, was to transform theorganisation of equity trading, allowing participants both toperform a banking role and to trade in equities, he said. Reuter&#3;